-- Russia Stocks Climb First Day in Four on Crude, Severstal Profit
-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 2012-04-19T15:41:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-19/russia-stocks-climb-first-day-in-four-on-crude-severstal-profit.html
Russian stocks advanced for the
first time in four days as oil jumped the most this month and
OAO Severstal’s earnings beat analyst estimates.  The  Micex Index (VTBMICX)  of 30 shares rallied 1.9 percent to
1,496.60 by the end of trading in Moscow, its biggest daily
increase since March 11. Severstal,  Russia ’s second-largest
steelmaker, surged 5.7 percent, its strongest advance since Jan.
3 and the biggest gainer on the Micex gauge today.  The Russian
Depositary Index (RDXUSD)  of London-traded shares of Russian companies
added 2 percent to 1,762.32.  Urals crude, Russia’s main export earner, added 1 percent
to $115.11 a barrel, its best advance since April 2. Oil and gas
account for about 50 percent of Russian government revenue.
Severstal said its fourth-quarter profit climbed 7.9 percent to
$463 million, beating the average analyst estimate of $390
million.  OAO Rosneft, Russia’s biggest oil company, rose 2 percent
to 215.35 rubles, its highest level since March 16, after
Citigroup Inc. upgraded the stock to buy from neutral and made
it its “top pick” today. OAO Lukoil, the country’s second-
largest oil producer, rose 1.5 percent to 1,800.70 rubles, its
first gain since April 11.  The  Market Vectors Russia ETF (RSX) , a U.S.-traded fund that
holds Russian shares, rose 2 percent to $30.22 in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denis Maternovsky in Moscow at 
